  "articleBody": "<!-- Page 2 --><article>\n\n    <h2 id=\"description\" class=\"yellow\">description of the work</h2>\n\n    <figure>\n      <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-280.webp 280w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-380.webp 380w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-480.webp 480w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-640.webp 640w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-840.webp 840w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1280.webp 1280w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1600.webp 1600w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, View of the opened triptych, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, View of the opened triptych, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" class=\"class-70-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"338\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-280.jpg 280w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-380.jpg 380w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-480.jpg 480w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-640.jpg 640w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-840.jpg 840w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1280.jpg 1280w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1600.jpg 1600w,\n      /docs/saint-jean/saint-jean_4-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>the opened triptych</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n      <p>We first describe what <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">the work represents</span> and for that we follow <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">the path of the gaze</span>, starting with the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">main scene</span>.</p>\n\n\n\n      <h3 id=\"couronnement\" class=\"yellow\">coronation of the virgin</h3>\n\n\n        <p>In the center, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">virgin Mary</span> thrones on a gold seat in front of a clothed cloth and under a red velvet baldaquin.</p>\n\n\n      <figure>\n        <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-280.webp 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-380.webp 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-480.webp 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-640.webp 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-840.webp 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1280.webp 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1600.webp 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/vierge-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Virgin and child”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, détail du panneau central, la “Vierge et l'enfant Jésus”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"1137\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-280.jpg 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-380.jpg 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-480.jpg 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-640.jpg 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-840.jpg 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1280.jpg 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1600.jpg 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/vierge-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “Virgin and child”</figcaption>\n      </figure>\n\n\n        <p>She <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">is crowned “Queen of heaven” by two small dark blue angels</span> flying above her.</p>\n\n\n      <figure>\n        <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-280.webp 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-380.webp 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-480.webp 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-640.webp 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-840.webp 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1280.webp 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1600.webp 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Madonna and child”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Madonna and child”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" class=\"class-70-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"277\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-280.jpg 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-380.jpg 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-480.jpg 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-640.jpg 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-840.jpg 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1280.jpg 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1600.jpg 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/deux-anges-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “Madonna and child”</figcaption>\n      </figure>\n\n\n\n      <h3 id=\"jesus\" class=\"yellow\">jesus child</h3>\n\n\n        <p>On his knees, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Jesus child</span>, seatted, hold a apple with his left hand, and move from his right hand <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">a ring</span> to the finger of <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">a woman</span>, placed futher down and left of her, on the front.</p>\n\n\n      <figure>\n        <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-280.webp 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-380.webp 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-480.webp 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-640.webp 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-840.webp 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1280.webp 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1600.webp 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Coronation of the virgin”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, “Coronation of the virgin”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"1137\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-280.jpg 280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-380.jpg 380w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-480.jpg 480w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-640.jpg 640w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-840.jpg 840w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1280.jpg 1280w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1600.jpg 1600w,\n        /docs/saint-jean/enfant-jesus-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, “Coronation of the virgin”</figcaption>\n      </figure>\n\n\n\n</article>"
